This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and President Macron during a state visit at the White House. President Trump thanks President Macron for his support in taking action against the Syrian regime's use of chemical weapons and expresses condolences to the Canadian people following a recent tragedy in Toronto. He also highlights the historic friendship between the United States and France, dating back to the American Revolution and World War I. President Macron emphasizes the enduring bond between the two countries and discusses their shared values and challenges, including terrorism, arms proliferation, prosperity, and environmental issues. He emphasizes the importance of working together to resist aggressive nationalism and build a strong multilateralism. Both presidents express their commitment to the friendship between their countries and their shared goals for the future.